race.description: The 50 Years Of Phil Chambers Maiden Plate
race.comment: ENDLESS ELLIEGANCE (6) is a 4YO who took a long time to get to the jumpouts, but has shown talent in the two she has participated in and from the inside draw she should be in the firing line for a long way. DAD BOD (1) produced a nice effort on debut in better company last start over 1100m at Mortlake when second, beaten half a length. Breaks from a wide draw but he can feature again. HI TIAGO (8) showed enough class in her debut campaign with all three runs on the Synthetic at Ballarat. Her recent jumpout win was solid and she ticks plenty of boxes first-up today. Can make a positive return. HOLLOW TURF (2) is better than we've seen at his past couple and has won a jumpout since his latest effort. Blinkers go on now and improvement is on the cards.
